The 2019–20 season of the &lt;a href="Slovenian%20Women%27s%20League"&gt;Slovenian Women's League&lt;/a&gt; (&lt;a href="Slovene%20language"&gt;Slovenian&lt;/a&gt;: Prva slovenska ženska nogometna liga) or simply 1. SŽNL was the 28th season of Slovenia's premier women's &lt;a href="Association%20football"&gt;football&lt;/a&gt; league. It ran from 18 August 2019 to 7 March 2020, when play was suspended. In May 2020 the season was cancelled due to the &lt;a href="COVID-19%20pandemic%20in%20Slovenia"&gt;COVID-19 pandemic in Slovenia&lt;/a&gt;. The executive board of the &lt;a href="Football%20Association%20of%20Slovenia"&gt;Football Association of Slovenia&lt;/a&gt; decided that defending champions and unbeaten league-leaders &lt;a href="%C5%BDNK%20Pomurje"&gt;ŽNK Pomurje&lt;/a&gt; would take the &lt;a href="2021%E2%80%9322%20UEFA%20Women%27s%20Champions%20League"&gt;2021–22 UEFA Women's Champions League&lt;/a&gt; place. 
